    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-08-31T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-08-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="437"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d437">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/2536</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        British Chargé</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_BCAR1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Barclay</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Memorandum</hi>
                </p>
                <p>The Secretary of State has the honor to acknowledge the receipt of the memorandum
                    of His Majesty’s Chargé d’Affaires, of August 16, 1918,<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d437fn1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_349">p. 349</ref>.</note>
                    informing him of the instructions sent by the British Government to the British
                    Consul at Vladivostok in connection with the methods deemed essential by the
                    British Government in order to establish order in that city; and further
                    requesting that, if this Government concur, similar instructions be sent to the
                    American representatives at Vladivostok.</p>
                <p>The Department of State has been happy to take under consideration the
                    suggestions advanced by His Britannic Majesty’s Chargé d’Affaires.</p>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-08-31">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 31, 1918</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
